sort (coreutils) 4.5.3

From: Bobby L Morris Subject: sort (coreutils) 4.5.3 Date: Wed, 25 Jun 2003 19:52:01 -0400

When I sorted a file with the sort command that is distributed with Red Hat Linux 9, ( /bin/sort from package coreutils 4.5.3) the output file was not consistent with the result obtained by using the sort command from another Unix system (AIX 5L). Also when I used the perl sort function I got the same results as when I used AIX 5L. Attached you will find: 1. unsorted_sig.txt - the unsorted input file 2. rhl9_sorted_sig.txt - the result of using the Red Hat Linux 9 sort command to sort the input file 3. aix5_sorted_sig.txt - the result of using the AIX 5L sort command to sort the input file. Bobby Morris
